“…they slipped briskly into an intimacy from which they never recovered...”
Cocktails, Dinner and Dancing immediately to follow

The Fox Theater is located at 241 South Main Street in Old Town Salinas. It first opened in November 1921 and was used for movie attractions for many years. In 2004 The Papering Theater rented out the Fox as a venue for their theatrical productions. It was there that Amy and Julian met and fell in love while working on the production of  ‘The Rocky Horror Show.’ In 2007, the theater was purchased by Anthony Lane and renovated to its present state.  The theater boasts a stage, dance floor, balcony with theater seats and two Art Deco bars. Amy and Julian’s wedding date is 11 years to the date that they started dating and they are excited to be getting hitched at the place where it all began.
View our Save the Date video here

A block of rooms have been reserved for Friday October 16th and Saturday October 17th at Hampton Inn and Suites in Salinas for a discounted rate of $149.00/night. The hotel is 3.3 miles away from the Fox Theater and offers free hot breakfast, high speed internet, access to a fitness center and parking.  If you are planning on staying at this hotel, we recommend booking the room as soon as possible as rooms are limited. Let them know your part of the Nelson/Faras wedding.
           Please note that all rooms must be reserved by September 17th.
